If $a < 2,$ then $h(0) < 0.$  Since $h(x)$ is continuous, and $\lim_{x \to \infty} h(x) = \infty,$ $h(x)$ takes on the value 0 for some $x > 0.$  Since $h(x)$ is even, $h(x)$ also takes on the value 0 for some $x < 0.$  This means the graphs of $f$ and $g$ intersect at at least two points.

